      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Although I am new to these boards, I find it very hard to swallow that the person supposedly representing the cleric community holds such unrepresentative views on the concerns of our class, and I certainly hope anyone claiming to speak for all has enough integrity to communicate all the issues being put out there.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That being said, I look at the issue from a "class balance" perspective. Shaman and druids are priests and therefore from the same overall class. They pay no reagent cost for their best buffs - nines and focus. To say cleric buffs are powerful is true, but no more so than the other priests spells, so in the interest of balance let's make this go away ASAP. Using that same pure class balance argument, AotZ and focus should stack so that we are again not the only priest class being penalized. It is not about whether these buffs are required or convenient, nor about reagent costs in general. I have no issue with emeralds being used for Divine Intervention since it is in-game to give a particular advantage in a particular situation and the cost is one of the trade-offs. And this is not a "want" or "wish" but a gross imbalance that should be fixed.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
